# Tic Tac Toe Game in Python

## Project Overview
This is a command-line Tic Tac Toe game implemented in Python. It allows two players to play the classic game of Tic Tac Toe, with input validation and real-time board updates after each move.

## Features
- Two-player gameplay (no AI)
- Input validation to prevent invalid moves
- Displays the game board after every move
- Detects win or draw conditions
- Clear and user-friendly command-line interface

## How to Run
1. Make sure you have Python 3 installed on your system.
2. Download or clone this repository.
3. Open a terminal or command prompt in the project directory.
4. Run the game with the command:
5. Follow the on-screen instructions to play.

## How to Play
- Players take turns entering a position number (1-9) corresponding to the board layout:

- The first player uses "X" and the second player uses "O".
- The game ends when a player wins or when all spots are filled (draw).

